&quot;, &quot;LECTOTYPE 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Tenthredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tenthredo eglanteriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eglanteriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tenthredo eglanteriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fabricius, 1793 des. SMBlank 2008&quot; [red, printed], &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus eglanteriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eglanteriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus eglanteriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(F.) = 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus bajulus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bajulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus bajulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Serv. [handwritten] det. S.M.Blank 2008 ✓&quot; [printed], &quot; ZMUC-GISHym 1014&quot;, &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1871" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus aericeps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aericeps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus aericeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Thomson, 1871 M.Heidemaa det.&quot; [printed]. Left hind tarsus and some other tarsomeres missing. ZMUC.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
Among 2♀ and 1♂ specimens preserved in the ZMUC collection under the name 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. eglanteriae" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="eglanteriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">T. eglanteriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, only the above female can be regarded as a syntype. The scutellum of the other female is red, and the tip of the abdomen of the male black. Both characters conflict with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Fabricius’">Fabricius'</normalizedToken>
original description. Compared with the other two specimens, the pale parts of the legs of the lectotype are darkened. The lectotype agrees with the species which has for a long time been known as 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1871" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus aericeps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aericeps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus aericeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Thomson, 1871 (
<bibRefCitation author="Zhelochovtsev, AN" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B199" refString="Zhelochovtsev, AN, 1994. [Translation of the book published in Russian in 1988]. In: Medvedev GS (Ed.) Keys to the Insects of the European Part of the USSR. Volume III Hymenoptera Part VI Symphyta. E.J. Brill, Leiden" title="[Translation of the book published in Russian in 1988]. In: Medvedev GS (Ed.) Keys to the Insects of the European Part of the USSR. Volume III Hymenoptera Part VI Symphyta. E. J." year="1994">Zhelochovtsev 1994</bibRefCitation>
), characterized for example by the laterally directed and distally curved setae of the ovipositor sheath. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lacourt, J" journalOrPublisher=")" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="77 - 108" refId="B105" refString="Lacourt, J, 2000. Liste des especes de la famille des Tenthredinidae decrites par J. G. Audinet-Serville, en Mai 1823 et par A. L. M. Le Peletier Comte de Saint-Fargeau, en Aout 1823, avec designation de lectotypes [Hymenoptera, Symphyta]. Revue francaise d'Entomologie (N. S.) 22 (2-3): 77 - 108" title="Liste des especes de la famille des Tenthredinidae decrites par J. G. Audinet-Serville, en Mai 1823 et par A. L. M. Le Peletier Comte de Saint-Fargeau, en Aout 1823, avec designation de lectotypes [Hymenoptera, Symphyta]. Revue francaise d'Entomologie (N. S." volume="22" year="2000">Lacourt (2000)</bibRefCitation>
used the name 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. bajulus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="bajulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. bajulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Serville, 1823 for this species, but 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2254.1.1" author="Blank, SM" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 96" refId="B20" refString="Blank, SM, Taeger, A, Liston, AD, Smith, DR, Rasnitsyn, AP, Shinohara, A, Heidemaa, M, Viitasaari, M, 2009. Studies toward a World Catalog of Symphyta (Hymenoptera). Zootaxa 2254 (1): 1 - 96, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2254.1.1" title="Studies toward a World Catalog of Symphyta (Hymenoptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2254.1.1" volume="2254" year="2009">Blank et al. (2009)</bibRefCitation>
presented arguments for the use of the name 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. aericeps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="aericeps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. aericeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(nomen protectum) versus 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. bajulus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="bajulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. bajulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(nomen oblitum). 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Tenthredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tenthredo eglanteriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eglanteriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tenthredo eglanteriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. germanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="germanica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">T. germanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Klug, F" journalOrPublisher="Der Gesellschaft Naturforschender Freunde zu Berlin Magazin fuer die neuesten Entdeckungen in der gesamten Naturkunde" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B80" refString="Klug, F, 1819. Die Blattwespen (Tenthredo Linn.) der Fabricischen Sammlung. Zoologisches Magazin (herausgegeben von C. R. W. Wiedemann) 1[1817-1819](3): 64-91." title="Die Blattwespen (Tenthredo Linn.) der Fabricischen Sammlung. Zoologisches Magazin (herausgegeben von C. R. W. Wiedemann) 1 [1817 - 1819] (3): 64 - 91." year="1819">Klug (1819)</bibRefCitation>
and with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.G.Thomson" authorityYear="1870" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Athalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Athalia glabricollis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabricollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Athalia glabricollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Thomson, 1870 by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.12830" author="Konow, FW" journalOrPublisher="Wiener entomologische Zeitung" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 18" refId="B94" refString="Konow, FW, 1897a. Synonymische Bemerkungen zu bisher nicht oder unrichtig gedeuteten Tenthredo Arten bei Geoffroy, Fabricius, Schrank und Villers. Wiener entomologische Zeitung 16: 1 - 18, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.12830" title="Synonymische Bemerkungen zu bisher nicht oder unrichtig gedeuteten Tenthredo Arten bei Geoffroy, Fabricius, Schrank und Villers." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.12830" volume="16" year="1897 a">Konow (1897a)</bibRefCitation>
. Since 
<bibRefCitation author="Brulle, A" journalOrPublisher="Ecological Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B25" refString="Brulle, A, 1846. Tome Quatrieme. In: Lepeletier de Saint-Fargeau (Ed.) Histoire naturelle des Insectes. Hymenopteres. Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret, Paris, 680 + 16 pp. [plates 37-48]" title="Tome Quatrieme. In: Lepeletier de Saint-Fargeau (Ed.) Histoire naturelle des Insectes. Hymenopteres. Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret, Paris, 680 + 16 pp. [plates 37 - 48]" year="1846">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Brullé">Brulle</normalizedToken>
(1846)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. eglanteriae" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="eglanteriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">T. eglanteriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(nomen oblitum) has never again been used as valid, while between 1971-2021 the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1871" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus aericeps" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aericeps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus aericeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(nomen protectum) was used as valid by more than 120 authors in over 150 publications (Article 23.9.1, 
